-- Poland’s PKN Orlen Said to Obtain $403 Million One-Year Loan
-- B y   L o u i s e   M e e s o n
-- 2012-03-29T16:25:48Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-29/poland-s-pkn-orlen-said-to-obtain-403-million-one-year-loan.html
PKN Orlen SA (PKN) , Poland’s largest oil
refiner, obtained a $403 million loan, according to a person
with direct knowledge of the deal.  The one-year deal is secured by one of the company’s oil
storage facilities, the person said, who declined to be
identified because the terms are private.  Royal Bank of Scotland Plc was sole bookrunner and arranger
on the deal which also involved HSBC Bank Plc, Bank of Tokyo-
Mitsubishi UFJ Ltd and  Bank Pekao SA. (PEO)   To contact the reporter on this story:
Louise Meeson in London on 
 lmeeson@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Faris Khan at 
 Fkhan33@bloomberg.net . 